This paper involves the use of deep learning for attacks on wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the use of adversarial deep learning, which involves the use of machine learning techniques to attack other machine learning systems, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of wireless networks, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of dynamic defenses, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques for attacks, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
